Caption: 5.4 A The pain of seeing and knowing yet not being able to reach, to touch, to be a part of, to be enveloped in, to be absorbed by, the separation, no longer in blind ignorance and feeling-less unreality but seeing and knowing and yet feeling the gulf between. Is this the final pain before the unity? Is this the last agony before the joining together? Must the devil rend us before we will relinquish us and let us return in body, mind, soul and essence. Complete to where we belong, the being cries in helpless despair to its Creator but where to begin to be free from the pain of separation? We long to take the final step, to be finally united and absorbed but what is the first step? We see the ultimate, we know the completion but what is the link between now and then? Between here and there. How do we begin to traverse the link? The final step is outside the bounds of our human identification but the first step must be inside it, because that is where we are now and always. Knowledge is the key. Each step is a grain of meaningful awareness. Nothing else is truly valid and action is the fruit of knowledge but knowledge is always the source, Something we must know to begin the journey towards the light but what is now? What is here for us? What are we, here and now for ourselves and others? #self #spirituality #spiritualawakening #spiritualjourney

Caption:
5 simple hacks to break through FEAR ğŸ‘‡ğŸ‘‡
.
.
Fear can be a powerful inhibitor and breaking through fear is often about taking action despite feeling afraid, rather than waiting for the fear to disappear entirely.
Here are five simple hacks to help you along your journey:

1. Visualization: Imagine yourself successfully overcoming whatever it is you fear. Visualize the process and the outcome vividly, including how you feel afterward. This can help reduce anxiety and build confidence.

2. Take Small Steps: Break down the task or situation that you fear into smaller, manageable steps. Focus on completing each step one at a time, gradually exposing yourself to the fear in a controlled way. This incremental approach can make the overall challenge feel less daunting.

3. Reframe Fear as Excitement: Sometimes, fear and excitement can feel quite similar physiologically. When you feel fear, try reframing it as excitement instead. Tell yourself that your body is preparing to take on a thrilling challenge rather than something to be afraid of.

4. Practice Mindfulness: Fear often arises from dwelling on the past or worrying about the future. Practice mindfulness techniques, such as deep breathing or meditation, to bring your focus to the present moment. This can help reduce anxiety and allow you to approach the situation with a clearer mind.

5. Seek Support: Don't be afraid to reach out to a professional for support. Talking about your fears with someone you trust can help alleviate some of the burden and provide valuable perspective and encouragement.

Your spiritual Coach,
Sharon Jackson

Caption:
Directed: Spenser Cohen, Anna Halberg
Release Date: May 3 
Rating: â˜…
Genre: Horror

I don't even know where to start with this film. It is stupid. The jump scares don't really get me. I was laughing and feeling more frustrated than scared. I won't spoil anything but the hangman scene involving a car. It was a moment that made me. Switch of my brain solely relying on my instinct to continue watching this film, and I still screamed out, "WHAT...really."

The best way to describe this film is as a result of a desperate brainstorming session. It feels like a bunch of film writers had less than 24 hours to pitch an idea to the studio. They resorted to using ChatGTP and TikTok, and the result was a mishmash of ideas. The film seems to have been inspired by a lot of tarot card readings on TikTok, and the combination of these elements resulted in a disjointed plot. While some of the performances were commendable, others left much to be desired. 

Overall watch this film with friends, while drunk and some pizza. Don't pay full price. It doesn't deserve your crash.

Caption:
DAY 3 OF 30:
Altar #1 of 12: Awakening Altar

Part 3 of 3: There is also much verdant plant life on this Altar as the Korean Chosun Dynasty chest it sits on faces the north facing window. The bamboo shoots are centrally placed and represent our Tree of Life. There are also two orchids (one is blooming), a succulent, a Money Tree and a Terrarium which we spritz each day and all else each week.

Our late cat Karmaâ€™s ashes are also placed on this Altar as it is also a celebration of his Life well lived in Light and Love with us. Not to mention that Ceylon loves to suntan on her new cat condo near here too. To speak of everything that is on this Altar would take pages. Letâ€™s focus on just one for now.

Our Bamboo Shoot Tree of Life is very much central to our Awakening Path as One will die multiple deaths (societal labels) in the Dark Night of the Soul before One is reborn into what One has always been. Each here is a Tree of Life in Spirit walking the phenomenal plane in physical form.

Oneâ€™s feet are the roots and need to be firmly grounded in Oneâ€™s Physical Body. Oneâ€™s body is the trunk supporting Oneâ€™s Spiritual Path that allows Oneâ€™s Astral Body to travel (as needed) and return to bodily form with the aforementioned firm grounding. Oneâ€™s head is the canopy where Oneâ€™s Casual Body connects back to Source at the beginning, during and at the end of Oneâ€™s life.

When in Oneâ€™s Physical Body, One is learning the lessons One needs to learn through the Divine Game of Leela (Lila). The play of dualism and separation where One is the Light one day or in one life and the dark in another day and another life or in the same day and life potentially. A Sacred Balance is eventually achieved and the two halves become whole Within One. The Game then ends and One becomes the Observer, no longer participating in the role play as the lessons have all been learned. 

One sees the truth and receives a new calling from Source to walk the remainder of Oneâ€™s Life path with Him side-by-side.

Until tomorrow â€¦ Light and Love in this Life â€¦ â¤ï¸ğŸ™â¤ï¸

Caption:
Seksueel misbruik is een vreselijke daad die diepe wonden achterlaat, niet alleen op emotioneel en mentaal vlak, maar ook op fysiek en energetisch niveau. Het heeft een verwoestend effect op het lichaam en kan leiden tot langdurige traumaâ€™s en problemen met seksuele intimiteit.

Het lichaam onthoudt het trauma van seksueel misbruik op een diep niveau, zelfs als het bewustzijn er niet altijd toegang toe heeft. Dit kan zich manifesteren in fysieke symptomen zoals chronische pijn, spanning, ongemak tijdens seksuele activiteiten en problemen met intimiteit en vertrouwen.

Op energetisch niveau kan seksueel misbruik de natuurlijke stroom van energie in het lichaam verstoren, waardoor blokkades ontstaan die de levenskracht belemmeren. Deze blokkades kunnen zich uiten in gevoelens van schaamte, schuld, angst en verwarring, waardoor het moeilijk wordt om een gezonde relatie met je eigen seksualiteit en die van anderen te ontwikkelen.

Het is belangrijk om te erkennen dat de impact van seksueel misbruik vaak diep geworteld is in het onderbewustzijn en dat het tijd en moed vergt om deze traumaâ€™s te helen. Het is essentieel om hulp en ondersteuning te hebben om dit proces te begeleiden en te genezen.

Het is ook belangrijk om te weten dat je niet alleen bent en dat er hulp beschikbaar is. Wees mild voor jezelf en weet dat je recht hebt op een gezonde en liefdevolle relatie met je eigen lichaam en seksualiteit.

Laat seksueel misbruik niet langer de controle over je leven hebben. Zoek hulp, sta jezelf toe om te helen en herstel je verbinding met je lichaam, je energie en je seksualiteit. Je verdient het om gezond en gelukkig te zijnâ¤ï¸

Caption:
Who usually attends your festivals? 

Solo guests? families? Large groups? Men? Women?

Absolutely all of the above and everything in between, we have a big emphasis on being family friendly hence we are inviting Kids for free. We also have some groups coming that have chosen our festival as a meet up and are creating their own little lounge area for their community. If you are differently-abled then you can bring your carer for free. We aim to be as inclusive as possible and make everyoneâ€™s stay as comfortable as we can. There are two different glamping options to suit as many needs as possible in the form of family friendly glamping yurts and a particularly funky glamoing Bus called â€˜Scarangarâ€™ which takes care of all your needs during the festival in VIP style. Regular camping is free of course and live in vehicles are welcome.There are lots of people who fly solo at our events as they say they meet more people when they come alone, some say they prefer it as it forces them to be sociable and make the most of the incredible well-being offerings and epic musicians. We are all one big happy family, so by the end of the weekend we hope thatâ€™s how everyone will feel. This is one of the benefits of it being a smaller and more intimate gig than some of the bigger events.

Todayâ€™s affirmation is â€œI am strong.â€ How to use affirmations:

Write post it notes and stick them where you often look (vanity, mirrors, laptop, fridge)

Write them in a journal or notebook (for journals and affordable notebooks check our page)

Caption:
"In the Qabalah, the Serpent of Wisdom refers to the direction or course of the Hebrew letters as placed on the twenty-two Tarot paths of the Thirty-Two Paths of Wisdom. Together, these paths form a symbolâ€”the Serpent of Wisdom. Therefore, the Tarot paths equal the Serpent of Wisdom while the Sephiroth equal the Path of the Flaming Sword. As the Path of the Flaming Sword represents Creation descending from the highest to the lowest (Kether to Malkuth), the Serpent of Wisdom climbs the Tree of Life from the lowest path (Tav) to the highest path (Aleph). You can see now how the symbology of the Serpent is present within the Qabalah and the Tree of Life. It is the Kundalini energy that lights up the entire Tree of Life when awakened. It is the Serpent that tempted Eve to eat of the Tree of Knowledge of Good and Evil in the Garden of Eden, even though God strictly forbade this. Through their disobedience to God, Adam and Eve were banished out of the Garden. Now, it is this Serpent again through whom we are to return to the Garden of Eden. We do so by awakening the Kundalini, the process of which is synonymous with activating and invigorating the entire Tree of Life and travelling upwards in consciousness. We ascend the Tree of Life in succession upwards, starting with the lowest Sephira, Malkuth, and ending with the highest Sephira, Kether." -Excerpt from "The Magus: Kundalini and the Golden Dawn" by Neven Paar

Caption:
So pleased to have the beautiful Emily Cobie and Friends join us for the Elemental Temple celebrations this year. Emily Cobie is a student of Bhakti Yoga, the practice of devotional yoga. Her mission is to share the power of Mantra and chanting, mainly through Kirtan, as a way to connect to divinity and collective consciousness.
 
She began learning Mantra 8 years ago with her Teacher Ajay Kumar through Vedic Chanting in his Shala, Shtalam 8 -Ashtanga & Vedanta Centre. Since then, Emily has been inspired and honoured to be a student of Sheela Bringi, a devotional Indian and Raga singer. She has also learnt from Kirtan leaders such as Sivani Mata and Ahisha Dasi. After spending time with Radhika Das and Friends in the holy place, Vrindavan, Emily has spent the last year sharing Kirtan in Buckinghamshire and numerous festivals and events in the UK. Emily holds a monthly Kirtan in Marlow as part of the Oh Shala Festival.
 
My core values lie in a practice of love, kindness, compassion and service in community. Through the medium of Kirtan we can call on divinity to open our hearts as we chant and sing together, weaving magic and collective healing.
@emily.cobie

Kundalini Activation Practice is a direct transmission from the kundalini field that supports the awakening of your own, innate, Kundalini energy.

This is an intelligent energy, and a safe, natural process that does just what your system needs and is ready for in any given moment.

This is an energy transmission, not a self-generated process, meaning you only need to lay back, relax, and receive in order to benefit from the practice.

This practice teaches surrender. Through surrender there is a unique possibility for healing, glimpses of higher states of consciousness that become more and more your everyday state, and a deeper connection to that which transcends mind and matter.

We gather every week to be in community, to continue opening and unfurling our deeper natures, to grow in consciousness, to develop ourselves, to strengthen our connection to the divine, and to commune with that loving intelligence which is the well spring of a greater reality.

In a class, you simply lie down, some music is played, and the facilitator holds the field. Your body and energy system activate in response, according to what is needed. It is a powerful, yet safe and gradual opening.

Caption:
PERUVIAN AGUA DE FLORIDA - MURRAY & LANMANâ€™S ORIGINAL FROM PERU ( Hard To Get )
 
A staple by healers and spiritual workers for its ability to attract good fortune, raise the vibration of whatever & whoever it comes into contact with, warding off negative energy and welcoming benevolent spirits.
 
Agua De Florida, translated is Florida Water. The name refers to the â€œFountain of Youthâ€, said to have been located in Florida. It is a cologne widely used by shaman all over South America for purification, cleansing, healing, and protection. Florida Water is toilette water that blends an array of floral essential oils in a water-alcohol base.
 
It has become popular worldwide, not only because of its delightful fragrance but also because of its many uses attributed to it. It has cleansing and protective properties to attract healing spirits. Shamans often place perfumes and colognes on the bodies of patients, as crosses on their forehead, chest, and back, while whistling a special song or Icaro of protection to seal, close, and protect the body. Florida Water is used by Shamans all over the world in their healing ceremonies.

Caption:
Iâ€™ve learned that going above and beyond for others who refuse to show up for you leads nowhere good. My time and energy are precious, so I cannot afford to waste them on one-sided relationships anymore, no matter how much history we share or how much I care about the person. 

I used to tolerate lying and cheating, thinking love could conquer all. But the truth is healthy relationships require mutual care, respect, effort, and communication. So now, if trust is broken through deceit or betrayal, I walk away no matter how difficult it is because I deserve faithfulness and honesty, no exceptions, no negotiations. 

Wishy-washy people, hot one day and cold the next, constantly keep you guessing where you stand. I have no place in my life anymore. The emotional rollercoaster is draining and damaging. I should never have to question if someone genuinely wants me in their life regularly. Consistent, committed caring is non-negotiable from here on out.

And if I express clearly that certain behaviors hurt me, but the person refuses to acknowledge responsibility or change, they have to go. Because promises without follow-through mean nothing. I cannot keep making excuses for unremorseful repeat offenses - thatâ€™s enabling more mistreatment. I have learned boundaries are the bedrock of healthy relationships. And my inner peace comes first now, above all else.

Caption:
THE THREAD OF DESIRE

What do you desire?  Deeply? Richly? With your whole Being?

Underneath the thinking you know about?  Underneath your invisible thinking? Underneath what you were taught to desire or not desire?  Underneath dogma? Underneath parental conditioning? Underneath cultural conditioning? 
 
When the heart speaks, and you listen with full acceptance and surrender, from the Ground of Being, what do you long for? If the desires are beyond your ego, where do they originate?

Iâ€™ve been listening to my heart and its desires with special attention in the past couple of days.  I have done this many times before.  But I have wondered â€“ are the desires of the heart in the afternoon of life different from those of dawn, of morning?

Caption:
What comes up when you find yourself resistant?
.
.
Navigating resistance, whether in personal development, work environments, or interpersonal relationships, requires a combination of strategies. 
Here are some effective approaches to get you started.

1. Understand the Root Cause: Identify why resistance is occurring. It could be due to fear, lack of understanding, conflicting interests, or previous negative experiences.

2. Communicate Openly: Engage in open and honest dialogue. Listen actively to understand concerns and provide clear, transparent information.

3. Empathy and Validation: Show empathy towards those who are resisting (especially if it's YOU). Validate their (YOUR) feelings and concerns, which can build trust and openness (W/YOURSELF).

4. Celebrate Small Wins: Break down changes into manageable steps and celebrate small victories. This can build momentum and demonstrate progress.

5. Be Patient and Persistent: Understand that overcoming resistance takes time. Be patient and consistently apply strategies to address it.

6. Adapt and Be Flexible: Be willing to adjust your approach based on feedback and changing circumstances. Flexibility can help find solutions that work for everyone.

7. Lead by Example: Demonstrate the behaviors and attitudes you want to see in others. Leading by example can inspire others to follow suit.

Caption:
Need help manifesting your dreams? Let's explore the power of way to manifest! âœ¨

Manifestation begins with getting crystal clear on your intentions and focusing your energy towards them. When you know exactly what you want to call in, you open the path for it to flow. 
 
Here are some tips for powerful intention-setting: 
1) Get specific on what you desire (job, relationship, home, etc.) 
2) Write it down and read it daily 
3) Create a vision board to visualize it 
4) Take inspired action steps towards your goal 
5) Let go and trust the universe's timing 

 Anchor your intentions with conviction and faith. What are you calling into your reality?

 And for those feeling a tad overwhelmed, I've got your back. Dive even deeper by joining the Inner Circle!!! By joining my monthly subscription community, you will have access to our monthly manifestation ritual, and our first one will be coming up in just a few days! DM me for more info!!!

Caption:
One very special Thriver brought this as a gift to me straight from her travels in Egypt! She sent me a picture of the man she watched carve this stone and as she handed it to me I got a glimpse of its magnificence. When I held it, it was like my being was instantly teleported to Egypt. It was like I was familiar with it and I began vibrating along with it. Pictures do not do it justice. This stone is called Alabaster. 
The use of alabaster can be traced back to ancient civilizations, including the Egyptians, Greeks, and Romans, who employed it extensively in their artistic and architectural endeavors. In ancient Egypt, alabaster was considered a precious stone and was used to create intricate carvings, statues, and vessels for religious and funerary purposes.
I am so touched to have received this and so excited about how it makes me feel.
Do you have a stone that makes you feel powerful or different when you hold it?
Do tell...

Warmly,
Stephanie The Medium

Caption:
Sushumna begins in the coccyx and runs up the Filum Terminale until it reaches Conus Medullaris. It continues through the fibre in the central canal, past the Fourth Ventricle, and ends in the Third Ventricle area, namely the Thalamus and Hypothalamus that connects to it. The CSF gets electrically charged by awakened Kundalini energy, which rises up the spinal cord, systematically activating the Major Chakras until it reaches the higher brain centres. The CSF is the key to the anatomical changes that occur in the brain upon a Kundalini awakening. The nervous system transforms as well through the invigoration of the spinal nerves. The organs are affected by this infusion of Light energy, which explains why so many Kundalini awakened individuals report anatomical changes in their insides. When the Kundalini enters the brain through the Sushumna channel, it terminates in the Thalamus, energizing it. Simultaneously, the Ida and Pingala Nadis energize the Pineal and Pituitary Glands. Since Ida and Pingala terminate in the Pineal and Pituitary Glands, their activation creates a magnetic effect that projects a vibratory stream of energy towards the Thalamus. The unification of these masculine (Yang) and feminine (Yin) powers in the Thalamus enables a full opening of Ajna Chakra, followed by Sahasrara at the top of the head. Once the Kundalini reaches the Crown, the "I Am" component of the Self, the Higher Self, awakens in our consciousness. The potential of the Thalamus is maximized, making this brain centre a perfect antenna to outside vibrations. The consciousness expands to the Cosmic level, and instead of taking in only 10% of the stimuli from the environment, it can now experience the full 100%." -Excerpt from "Serpent Rising: The Kundalini Compendium" by Neven Paar

Caption:
Iâ€™ve been told I am â€˜too sensitiveâ€™ my entire life. Iâ€™ve felt an unexplainable depth of loneliness in most social settings. Iâ€™ve pissed off so many people by sharing what I can feel in their field even in the face of their denial. 

As a child, I remember speaking to â€˜peopleâ€™ out in the garden, but getting into trouble with my African nanny because that was taboo, so I stopped communicating with them, feeling naughty instead of connected and tapped in.

I predicted meeting Orlando Bloom at an airport when I was 12. I put a white tshirt & a permanent market into my handbag so that I could get his signature.. and a few hours later, I bumped right into him. But when I told this story, my friends thought I was lying.. so I stopped tuning into the pre-cognition, feeling shame instead of pride.

Iâ€™ve felt sadness with a stranger, so I asked her if she was ok. She burst into tears and literally ran away.  I stopped trusting the nudge, feeling guilty instead of supportive.

In my relationships, when Iâ€™ve felt that things were going on & raised them, Iâ€™ve been punished for my â€˜accusationsâ€™ - only to eventually be proven right. So I forced my intuition into a cage, feeling like it was â€˜my trust issuesâ€™ instead of someone elseâ€™s untrustworthiness.

Standard social settings drain me, because I canâ€™t stand small talk. So I slink into a corner alone or act awkwardly because I donâ€™t know how to communicate about the weather when I can feel a depth of pain and suffering inside the human in front of me.

Iâ€™ve tried to shut down this part of me, because itâ€™s caused me so much pain.

But what I am coming to realise,

Is that being an intuitive empath is a f*cking GIFT. 

Itâ€™s NEVER been about shutting myself down or trying to fit inâ€¦

But about finding the right environments to FLOURISH in, & the right people to flourish around.

And respectful ways to give your gift to others ğŸ¤£

Being highly sensitive, intuitive, spirituality gifted or an empath is something to nurture & respect, because when supported correctly, it can be a super power that can transform your life & lives of people you love.

Grateful for my @owakenbreathwork daily practice tuning me back IN.
Letâ€™s go.

Caption:
Artist is @charliemackesy 

I completed a session of past lives a few months ago and at the end of the session, I asked the higher self if it had any more information it wished to share with the client. 

It pretty much gave the message of my post (in fewer words though, I need to learn to be like a higher conscious mind! ğŸ˜‚). Talk about coincidence! 

Anyway here are my thoughts, inspired by this lovely picture and quote ğŸ˜Š....

There is a lot going on in the world at this moment, but always remember there is balance. â˜¯ï¸

So many of us are allowing the stories and narrative pull us down. 

There is often too much focus on negativity but not always enough focus on the incredible beauty and love that is abundant in this world and in people.

Donâ€™t let the negativity consume you. The fear, the hate the violence. 

Once we allow too much in, it limits our capacity to think positively. 

How can we help anyone, when our own minds are consumed with fear and negativity?

Deal with that which has direct impact on you. There will be times when we need to face our own challenges, and they may be tough. 

But be sure to heal by returning focus to positive and the good around us.

The information we consume effects us, so choose wisely where you place your attention.

Itâ€™s important we maintain our own balance for our own wellbeing. Only then can we make a positive impact on others and give help to those in need.

Caption:
Arkanaâ€™s 7 Pâ€™s of Integration- Practice Patience ğŸ¦‹

As you go back to your daily life after an Ayahuasca retreat, be patient with yourself and your own process. Rome wasn't built in a day. 

Not everything is going to change overnight.  You are adjusting to new ways of being with yourself and with your reality. Ayahuasca helps you gain new neuropathways, but these take time to unfold in yourself; part of integration is doing the work to strengthen them. Speaking to yourself kindly and gently allows those new pathways to really take root. ğŸ™ğŸ¼

Know that small changes are okay too. Start with baby steps, and slowly you will start to build some momentum and will notice lasting changes in you and those around you. 
Do something every day that will keep the flame going that the medicine ignited in you. ğŸ”¥

Donâ€™t be afraid of committing mistakes. Mistakes can be the best teachers if you learn from them and sometimes you have to let life cut your head off to get a new one. 

Being kind and gentle with yourself will take you much further in your path of healing and growth. Practicing patience goes hand in hand with trust, contentment, and confidence. 

Treat yourself gently and kindly to do the best and truest effort you can make and acknowledge yourself for it.

Caption:
You could change your life and the world. Any of us could utilize the tools at our disposal to create the lives we want to live, achieve great success, and offer our creations to the world. We only lack self-belief.

Everyone is born with that ability, regardless of circumstances, race, gender, or age. It is only a matter of when we decide to own our authentic selves whenever that might occur. That is self-actualization.

We don't know who we could become because it's always in front of us, so taking steps into the unknown is always the most frightening. Since I've been doing it for so longâ€”I'm 73 nowâ€”I can tell you the effects of what happens when you take those steps; you will discover your greatness. 

That is the story I will tell when I film Beyond Belief with George Noory this Friday for Gaia. I've held that idea for years because it was unbelievable to me and many others. But we stand at a place in our lives and the world when more of us must take self-empowerment steps.

It's hard to believe what is possible when we haven't done it. When we become willing to take those steps into self-discovery, we unveil our greatness. 

Your life was meant to change the world, which is why you were born. It's just a matter of you deciding to move through the barriers and blockages that have prevented you from becoming magnificent and living the life that you're supposed to have. Your creation will help change our world. 

I recorded this video earlier, which explains my process. We are never done, and mine will continue as well. https://youtu.be/lrKHi-Ebo1c

Caption:
We hope you all made it through your Monday unscathed ğŸ˜ Quick question for you fine people, do you know what a â€˜psychedelic experienceâ€™ is? Well, as per good old â€˜Wikipediaâ€™ we have the definition below for you if youâ€™re unsure â¬‡ï¸

â€˜A psychedelic experience (known as a trip) is a temporary altered state of consciousness induced by the consumption of a psychedelic substance For example, an acid trip is a psychedelic experience brought on by the use of LSD, while a mushroom trip is a psychedelic experience brought on by the use of psilocybin. Psychedelic experiences feature alterations in normal perception such as visual distortions and a subjective loss of self-identity, sometimes interpreted as mystical experiences. 

Psychedelic experiences lack predictability, as they can range from being highly pleasurable (known as a good trip) to frightening (known as a bad trip). The outcome of a psychedelic experience is heavily influenced by the personâ€™s mood, personality, expectations, and environment (also known as set and setting).â€™ âœ¨

Caption:
"When all my earlier ways of grasping had faded away, I came to rest in the spontaneous vastness of the ever-pure ground of being. In that moment, everything that arose as the creative expressions of that ground dissolved naturally back into that same expanse.

This primordial ground- together with its creative expressions, free of modification, antidote, meditation practice, memory, grasping, and identification-is called path pristine awareness.

This ultimate reality is most easily seen in the absence of mental activity. As hopes, fears, negation, and affirmation dissolve into absolute space, their quiescence reveals the self-emergent primordial consciousness, the timeless mode of the great dharmakÄya, free of all extremes, partiality, going, and coming.

Know that all appearances are the creative expressions of pristine awareness; they slip back into the essential nature, dissolving into the primordial womb like waves naturally subside back into the ocean..."

from "  Heart of the Great Perfection: Dudjom Lingpa's Visions of the Great Perfection, Vol. 1 " 
by B. Alan Wallace

Caption:
I used to throw these lavish birthday parties, you know? The kind that took weeks to plan and a small fortune to pull off. I told myself I loved doing it, but deep down, it was about the applause at the end of the dayâ€”the nods, the compliments, the 'wow' faces.

It's not just parties, though. Many of us fall into the trap of doing more to feel valued: longer hours at work, the perfect Instagram shot, the seamless persona. 

Society chants a constant refrain: do more, be more.

But hereâ€™s what Iâ€™ve learned: the real magic happens when we do less but with more presence. When we stop performing for others and start living for the moments themselves.

âœ¨ï¸Breaking the Cycle

ğŸŒ±Self-Reflection: Ask yourself, "Am I doing this for me or for the approval of others?" Honesty here is crucial.

ğŸŒ±Value Presence: Start valuing presence over praise. Be in the moment, whether itâ€™s a simple lunch or a walk in the park.

ğŸŒ±Set Boundaries:** Itâ€™s okay to say no to things that donâ€™t add value to your life. Doing less can often mean living more.

Take a moment to honestly assess where you might be performing or acting just for acknowledgment. This isn't about feeling guilty or ashamedâ€”it's about gaining awareness. Recognizing these patterns is the first step toward genuine self-expression and deeper personal satisfaction. Share your reflections, letâ€™s explore this awareness together.

Caption:
For the past 14 years Iâ€™ve been teaching people how to be happy, through best-selling books, retreats, and coaching, Iâ€™ve genuinely been happy doing what I love for a living; But one can be happy (in the light) and on a healing (in the dark) journey at the same time. 

For several years I silently suffered from unexplained weight gain, chronic body aches, panic attacks, complex migraines, depression, insomnia, and low self-worth. My personal life was turbulent. Trapped in codependent, toxic relationship connections, trying to make sense of, and break free from abusive narcissistic relationships, and heal from childhood trauma. It wasnâ€™t until I was diagnosed with Fibromyalgia, a chronic muscle pain condition did I make the connection between my diminishing mental health and degrading physical health. It became clear to me that I needed to heal, and radically change my life. This set me on a new path of self-discovery and a deeper sense of self-love... one now grounded in self-worth and respect, where my inner child was being held for the very first time.

I overhauled my entire life, by removing all toxicity, including the foods I ate, to where I lived (yep, remember that year I moved to Mexico.) I put up boundaries, stopped people pleasing, and started living for me (and my best friend, my rescue dog Chance). And I did save my own life! I havenâ€™t had a fibromyalgia flair in over two years. My BMI has gone down, my skin has cleared up and all that regular depression and anxiety I was used to living with has left the building.

I truly have a deeper love in my heart and self-awareness in my body, more so than I ever thought possible. I know life can be hard at times, but when we come together, and do the inner work, we support each other in love, we prevail. 

You got this, and I got you! You may ask how? I did it by showing up for me and saying I MATTER!  By utilizing the power of science and traditional practice and caring for me as a mother would, with ancient wisdom and homemade natural remedies, I transformed my life. See comments for How ğŸ‘‡

Caption:
Weekly Insight for June 2-8, 2024:

This week brings a powerful opportunity for personal transformation and spiritual evolution, as the alignment of the planets on June 3 signals a surge of energy that can propel you towards growth. It's a time to break free from old patterns and embrace the new, shedding what no longer serves you. The key is to align yourself with truth, trust, transformation, and surrender to the flow of life.

At the beginning of the week, with the moon transitioning through Aries and Taurus, take time to relax and find peace within. Connect with your true self and embrace your connection to others, nature, and the Divine. Avoid getting caught up in materialistic pursuits or negative emotions by practicing peace and selflessness. By midweek, with the Moon in Gemini, focus on making connections, communicating your truths, and enjoying life to the fullest. Embrace the natural cycles of joy and hardship, anchoring yourself in love and trust.

As the week progresses and the Moon moves into Cancer, embrace your emotions and allow yourself to heal old wounds. Spend time meditating and staying focused on what you truly want in life. The Divine Feminine within you is rising, so surrender to the flow of life and maintain balance in mind, body, and spirit. Remember that you are not alone and that you hold the Universe within you.

Overall, this week is a time of rebirth and transformation, guided by the higher self and the Divine. Embrace the changes and trust in the process, knowing that you are protected and supported on your journey. Stay positive, stay connected, and step into the blessings and opportunities that come your way.

Hello Collective! ğŸ¤ğŸ•Šï¸ğŸ¤

When a seed is planted, our intentions are emitted into it from the palm of our hands. Our energy transferred into this little seed, when buried into life giving soil, also takes root along with it, encouraging and nurturing it to grow. In this depth of earth, this dark expanse, this little seed is on its own, as are the intentions we planted along with it. It does not know its outcome, just that it is safely nestled in its womb, with the intent to grow.

As we water it, we leave it alone. For we know it has the wherewithal to take root on its own. So too must we embrace this void and trust that we have the tools and resources necessary to make our dreams our reality. We must trust ourselves, our intuition, and the Universe. We alone have the answers to our questions, and most times, we do not need to know. Release control and trust the process. Bloom into who you are meant to be. Embrace the void and free yourself from expectations, yearning, longing, and rumination. Listen to your soulâ€™s call, and release it all.
